  "texts": [
    "Lung tumors are divided into three groups from a histopathological perspective: small-cell lung cancer (SCLC), which also includes small-cell carcinoma; non-small-cell lung cancer (NSCLC); and other uncommon forms of tumors, which include sarcoma and lymphoma.",
    "Adenocarcinoma, squamous cell carcinoma, and large-cell lung cancer are the three subtypes of NSCLC [31].",
    "Smoking is crucial in identifying lung cancer since it plays a critical function in the disease [32].",
    "COVID-19A specific contagious lung disease that spreads to people exponentially is.",
    "COVID-19 symptoms include flu, cough, and shortness of breath."
  ]
